AnÃ¡lisis parameÌtrico o de sensibilidad aplicacioÌn MeÌtodo axiomaÌtico de Arrow y Raymond

intalpha = seq(0,0.5,0.1)
sol = vector("list",length(intalpha)) 
for (i in 1:length(intalpha)) {
    p_i = p
    p_i[1,] = p_i[1,] * intalpha[i]
    sej_i = multicriterio.metodoaxiomatico.ArrowRaymond(p_i)
    sol[[i]] = sej_i$alternativasordenadas} 
sol
## [[1]]
## [1] "a4" "a2" "a3" "a1"

## [[2]]
## [1] "a4" "a2" "a3" "a1"
## 
## [[3]]
## [1] "a4" "a2" "a3" "a1"
## 
## [[4]]
## [1] "a4" "a2" "a3" "a1"

## [[5]]
## [1] "a4" "a2" "a3" "a1"
## 
## [[6]]
## [1] "a4" "a2" "a3" "a1"
posiciones_a4 = rep(NA,length(intalpha)) 
for (i in 1:length(intalpha)) {
    posiciones_a4[i] = which(sol[[i]]=="a4")}
posiciones_a4
## [1] 1 1 1 1 1 1
plot(intalpha,posiciones_a4,type= "l") #RepresentaciÃ³n grÃ¡fica de estos cambios
